taining or not motion signal and (iii){\textbackslash}nvarying center-surround distance. Our experiments show that non-linear{\textbackslash}ninteractions between and within cor- tical areas lead to the modulation{\textbackslash}nof the {CRF}. Depending on stimulus char- acteristics, we observed{\textbackslash}na dynamical balance between fast facilitation and slower suppression{\textbackslash}nthat results from a strong interplay between horizontal and feedback{\textbackslash}nconnectivity. {\textbackslash}n{\textbackslash}{nAcknowledgement}: European integrated project {FACETS} {IST}-15879, Fédération{\textbackslash}ndes Aveugles et handicapés visuels de France},
